## 6. IMPLEMENTATION

### 6.1 SAMPLE CODE
*Middleware Implementation for Role & Token Protection ([authMiddleware.js](file:///c:/Users/srivani/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/server/middleware/authMiddleware.js)):*
```javascript
const protect = async (req, res, next) => {
    let token = req.headers.authorization?.split(' ')[1];
    if (token) {
        try {
            const decoded = jwt.verify(token, process.env.JWT_SECRET);
            req.user = await User.findById(decoded.id).select('-password');
            
            // Child fallback logic (Children use separate Mongo Collection)
            if (!req.user) {
                const child = await Child.findById(decoded.id);
                if (child) req.user = { _id: child._id, role: 'child', name: child.name };
            }
            
            if (!req.user) throw new Error('User not found');
            next();
        } catch (error) { 
            res.status(401).json({ message: 'Token failed or expired' }); 
        }
    } else {
        res.status(401).json({ message: 'Not authorized, no token' });
    }
};
```

### 6.2 OUTPUT SCREENS
*(Note: Visual representation map for implementation)*
1.  **Parent Dashboard Output:** Displays a customized greeting, the family invite code, a dynamic list of "Today's Activities" hyperlinked to granular schedules, and a "My Appointments" table charting real-time approval statuses.
2.  **Doctor Portal Output:** A dual-pane interface. Left pane charts pending daily appointments. Right pane lists the patient directory, spawning a "Full History Modal" detailing pending vaccines, age, weight percentiles, and prior appointment logs.
3.  **Child Media Center Output:** An immersive grid of embedded YouTube videos filtered by age. A persistent overhead banner dynamically counts down the remaining `Time Left`.

### 6.3 TEST CASES

| Test Case ID | Feature | Description | Expected Result | Status |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **TC_01** | **Authentication** | Parent registers a new account using valid email format. | Account created, JWT issued, redirected to Dashboard. | Pass |
| **TC_02** | **Doctor Portal** | Doctor clicks "View Full History" on a patient row. | Modal opens aggressively fetching health records and vaccine arrays from the database. | Pass |
| **TC_03** | **Child Login** | Child attempts login with correct Invite Code but invalid PIN. | API returns 401 Unauthorized; UI displays "Invalid PIN" alert. | Pass |
| **TC_04** | **Screen Time** | Child consumes media resulting in `screenTimeUsed` == `screenTimeLimit`. | React component state toggles; Video renders disappear and are replaced by the "Screen Time's Up!" lock screen. | Pass |
| **TC_05** | **Routing** | Child attempts to access URL `/dashboard` manually. | ProtectedRoute middleware catches role mismatch and forces redirect back to `/media`. | Pass |

---

## 7. CONCLUSION
The Baby Care Management System successfully integrates the multifaceted and complex challenges of modern parenting into a cohesive, secure digital platform. By unifying pediatric health tracking, simplifying the doctor-parent scheduling loop, and fully automating digital media constraints, the application provides immense utility to households. Furthermore, the robust MERN stack architecture ensures that the platform is scalable, secure, and highly performant. 

Future enhancements could involve migrating the React client to React Native for native mobile app distribution on Android/iOS, integrating AI-driven pediatric health insights based on historical growth metrics, and implementing automated push-notification arrays (via WebSockets or service workers) for immediate upcoming vaccination reminders.

